<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="922" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d922">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 761.91/55</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-16T17:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Department’s August 13, 6 p.m. Does new Persian Cabinet support
                            decree and attitude of late Persian Cabinet? Was action of late Persian
                            Cabinet relative to treaties instigated by Germans? Instruct <persName corresp="#p_SAE1">Southard</persName> also to investigate and report
                            his views.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>